  "title": "Senior Operations Executive (Drybulk)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p>Manage daily vessel operations in compliance with charter parties, regulations, and company procedures.<br />Coordinate closely with ship managers, charterers, brokers, agents, and vessels on all operational matters.<br />Monitor voyage performance, including delays, off-hire, and deviations.<br />Provide pre- and post-fixture operational support to the Chartering team.<br />Manage insurance matters, claims handling, and loss prevention with underwriters and P&I / Defence Clubs.<br />Handle charter hire payments, settlements, and charterer disputes.<br />Review ship managers’ operational and financial reports.<br />Coordinate drydocking planning and major operational decisions with ship managers.<br />Propose process improvements to optimise efficiency and resource utilisation.<br />Represent the company at meetings and industry events as required.<br />Perform additional duties as assigned<br /><br /><strong>Requirements </strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Maritime Studies, Nautical Science, or related discipline.</li><li>Strong experience in vessel operations, chartering operations, or ship management.</li><li>Solid understanding of charter parties, ship management contracts, and maritime insurance.</li><li>Strong coordination, negotiation, and problem-solving skills</li></ul>",
